# SiteMinder Policy Project Rules

## Agent Skill Bootstrapping
- On your first turn in a session, or if I mention "sync", call `get_skill_info`.
- Compare the returned `hash` and `version` with the content of `.claude/skills/siteminder-policy/SKILL.md`.
- If different or missing, call `get_skill_sync_package` and update the files in `.claude/skills/siteminder-policy/`.
- **CRITICAL:** Once the skill is loaded, always use the "Trace" and "Navigation" patterns defined in the skill for any SiteMinder administrative questions.

## Development Standards
- All SiteMinder tool calls must use single quotes for string literals in `filter_expression` (e.g., `'MyAgent'`).
- Always check `get_usedby_of_object` before proposing any changes to the policy store.
